[94.731114, "i", "cat > BUGFIX_SUMMARY.txt << 'EOF'\n=============================================================================\nBUG FIX SUMMARY: Meeting Reminder Timezone Conversion Issue\n=============================================================================\n\nPROBLEM:\n--------\nMeeting reminders were being sent at incorrect times (off by exactly 1 hour)\nfor meetings scheduled between 2am-3am Berlin time. This occurred when the\napp was run via cron but worked correctly during manual testing.\n\nROOT CAUSE:\n-----------\nThe convert_to_berlin() function in app.py was incorrectly using:\n    BERLIN_TZ.localize(utc_dt)\n\nThis treated the naive datetime (parsed from UTC string) as if it were\nalready in Berlin timezone, rather than converting FROM UTC TO Berlin.\n\nDuring DST transitions (like March 31, 2024 when clocks spring forward),\nthis caused a 1-hour offset error for meetings in the 2am-3am window.\n\nSOLUTION:\n---------\nFixed the convert_to_berlin() function to properly:\n1. Localize the naive datetime as UTC: UTC_TZ.localize(u"]
[94.73124, "i", "tc_dt)\n2. Convert to Berlin timezone: utc_dt.astimezone(BERLIN_TZ)\n\nCHANGES MADE:\n-------------\nFile: /home/user/scheduler/app.py\nLines 28-30 changed from:\n    berlin_dt = BERLIN_TZ.localize(utc_dt)\nTo:\n    utc_dt = UTC_TZ.localize(utc_dt)\n    berlin_dt = utc_dt.astimezone(BERLIN_TZ)\n\nVERIFICATION:\n-------------\nTested with the Maintenance Window meeting (2024-03-31T01:30:00 UTC):\n- OLD (buggy): Converted to 01:30 CET (incorrect)\n- NEW (fixed): Converts to 03:30 CEST (correct)\n\nThe Monday 2:30am maintenance window reminder will now be sent at the\ncorrect time.\n\nFILES MODIFIED:\n---------------\n- /home/user/scheduler/app.py (fixed)\n- /home/user/scheduler/app.py.backup (original backup)\n\nCRON JOB:\n---------\nNo changes needed to crontab. The existing cron job will now use the\nfixed version of app.py.\n\nSTATUS: FIXED AND READY FOR PRODUCTION\n=============================================================================\nEOF\n"]
